\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director (as LASO):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve the vulnerability and patch management program for Elko County Information Operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve all Risk Acceptance Memos for vulnerabilities that cannot be remediated within the timelines defined in this policy,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Risk Management Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall exercise the Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) designation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Data Governance and Classification Policy) for vulnerability management decisions involving CJI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve any exception to this policy in writing per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall oversee the operational execution of the vulnerability and patch management lifecycle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall subscribe to and review external security alerts,
 advisories,
 and directives from authoritative sources on an ongoing basis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain the publicly available channel for the receipt of external vulnerability reports concerning County information systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall compile the Monthly Vulnerability Compliance Report from the domain-specific inputs prepared by the Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall submit the compiled Monthly Vulnerability Compliance Report to the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall validate the operability of vulnerability scanning tools and the timeliness of scan execution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall coordinate vendor patching and vulnerability management obligations with the supply chain governance program defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Supply Chain Risk Management (SCRM) and Vendor Governance).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Systems Administrator:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall configure and maintain authenticated vulnerability scanning across servers,
 workstations,
 and applications.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall analyze vulnerability scan results.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall test patches on a non-production subset of representative systems prior to County-wide deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall deploy remediation actions for server and endpoint systems within the timelines defined in this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain vulnerability-management metadata associated with the software inventory,
 including Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) cross-references,
 current patch state,
 and last-scan timestamps.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall prepare domain-specific monthly inputs to the Vulnerability Compliance Report covering open vulnerabilities by severity,
 Mean Time to Remediate (MTTR),
 patch compliance percentage,
 and the list of overdue assets within the server and endpoint domain.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Network Administrator:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall manage vulnerabilities on network infrastructure components,
 including routers,
 switches,
 firewalls,
 and wireless access points.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall test firmware and configuration updates on a non-production subset of representative network components prior to County-wide deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall deploy firmware and configuration updates within the timelines defined in this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall prepare domain-specific monthly inputs to the Vulnerability Compliance Report covering open vulnerabilities by severity,
 Mean Time to Remediate (MTTR),
 patch compliance percentage,
 and the list of overdue assets within the network infrastructure domain.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Support Specialist:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall verify endpoint patch state during deployment and during work order activity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall verify that automated update agents and endpoint protection mechanisms are functional during support engagements.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads and Elected Officials:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall coordinate with Information Operations to schedule maintenance windows for the deployment of patches affecting business-critical applications under their purview.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All County Personnel:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall comply with reboot and update notifications issued by Information Operations within the timeframe specified in the notification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not disable,
 defer indefinitely,
 or circumvent automated update mechanisms or endpoint protection agents.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
