\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Hardware Inventory Source
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall scope vulnerability scanning to the asset inventory maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (IT Asset Management Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Software Inventory Source
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall scope patch targeting and vulnerability identification to the software inventory and the field set defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Vulnerability Management Augmentation
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall maintain vulnerability management metadata linked to each software inventory record.
 At a minimum,
 the augmentation set shall include the following:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CVE Cross-Reference
\series default
:
 The Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) identifiers known to affect the recorded software version.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Current Patch State
\series default
:
 The patch level installed on each instance,
 expressed as the vendor-defined version,
 build,
 or update identifier.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Last-Scan Timestamp
\series default
:
 The date and time of the most recent vulnerability scan that evaluated the recorded instance.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Security Advisories and Directives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Intake
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall subscribe to and review security alerts,
 advisories,
 and directives from authoritative external sources,
 including the Multi-State Information Sharing and Analysis Center (MS-ISAC),
 the Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA),
 the United States Computer Emergency Readiness Team (US-CERT),
 federal and state advisories,
 and vendor security feeds for products in the asset inventory.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Dissemination
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall route applicable advisories to the Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator within one (1) business day of receipt for review and applicability determination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Implementation
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall implement remediation actions identified in advisories or directives within the timelines established for the corresponding severity in this policy,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section SI-5 (Security Alerts,
 Advisories,
 and Directives).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Internal Generation
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall generate internal advisories where threat conditions affecting County assets warrant action beyond the scope of an external advisory.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Public Vulnerability Reporting Channel
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall maintain a publicly available email address for the receipt of vulnerability reports concerning County information systems from external sources,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section RA-5(11) (Public Disclosure Program).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall triage reports received through the public reporting channel under this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall escalate confirmed or suspected exploitation arising from a public vulnerability report under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Identification and Reporting Procedures).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Noncompliance Notification
\series default
:
 Where a directive cannot be implemented within the established timeframe,
 the Assistant IT Director shall notify the issuing organization of the degree of noncompliance and shall document the deviation in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Vulnerability Scanning and Identification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Automated Scanning
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall employ automated tools to perform vulnerability scans on all active assets within the scope of this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
External-Facing Systems
\series default
:
 For purposes of this policy,
 external-facing systems are systems,
 services,
 interfaces,
 gateways,
 web applications,
 application programming interfaces (APIs),
 mail gateways,
 and cloud services reachable from the public Internet or from networks not owned or operated by Elko County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Scanning Frequency
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall scan internal systems no less frequently than monthly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall scan external-facing systems no less frequently than weekly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall scan systems that process,
 store,
 or transmit CJI at the stricter of the monthly internal-systems baseline or the cadence required by CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section RA-5 (Vulnerability Monitoring and Scanning).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator or the Network Administrator shall initiate an ad-hoc scan within seventy-two (72) hours of the publication of a Critical severity vendor security advisory affecting County assets.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Scan Content Currency
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall update vulnerability scanning tool content within twenty-four (24) hours prior to each scheduled scan and upon receipt of notification of new vulnerabilities affecting County assets,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section RA-5(2) (Update Vulnerabilities to Be Scanned).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authenticated Scanning
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall perform vulnerability scans using privileged credentials.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall perform authenticated scans on all systems that process,
 store,
 or transmit CJI,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section RA-5(5) (Privileged Access).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator or the Network Administrator shall submit an exception under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 for any asset whose architecture does not support privileged-credential scanning.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Asset Discovery
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall configure scanning tools to identify devices connected to County networks and to flag devices that are not present in the asset inventory.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unauthorized Device Routing
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator or the Network Administrator who identifies through asset discovery a device that is not present in the asset inventory shall report the device as an Indicator of Compromise in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Vulnerability Scoring and Prioritization
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Scoring Standard
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall assess vulnerabilities using the Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) version 3.1 or a successor version adopted by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Severity Categories
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Critical
\series default
:
 CVSS base score of 9.0 through 10.0.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
High
\series default
:
 CVSS base score of 7.0 through 8.9.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Medium
\series default
:
 CVSS base score of 4.0 through 6.9.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Low
\series default
:
 CVSS base score of 0.1 through 3.9.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prioritization
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall prioritize remediation by combining the CVSS base score with the asset criticality classification defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and the asset support classification defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Patch Management and Remediation Timelines
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Remediation Mandate
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall test and deploy security patches,
 firmware updates,
 or compensating controls within the following timelines,
 measured from the date of vendor release or vulnerability discovery,
 whichever is earlier,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section SI-2 (Flaw Remediation):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Critical Severity
\series default
:
 Within fifteen (15) calendar days.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
High Severity
\series default
:
 Within thirty (30) calendar days.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Medium Severity
\series default
:
 Within sixty (60) calendar days.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Low Severity
\series default
:
 Within ninety (90) calendar days.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Patch Testing
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall test patches on a non-production subset of representative systems prior to County-wide deployment to identify operational impact.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Emergency Patch Testing
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exception
\series default
:
 The IT Director may authorize expedited patch deployment without full non-production testing where active exploitation of a Critical severity vulnerability creates immediate operational risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator or the Network Administrator shall document compensating monitoring and rollback steps within the Emergency Change record under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Change Management Policy).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Automated Updates
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall configure workstations and endpoints to install security-relevant updates automatically.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall obtain a Risk Acceptance Memo approved under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 for any deviation from automatic installation.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Change Authorization
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall authorize patch deployments in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator may implement patches as Standard Changes when a documented procedure exists in the Knowledge Base.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall follow the Emergency Change procedure for patching that cannot await standard authorization.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Isolation of Unremediated Critical Vulnerabilities
\series default
:
 The Network Administrator shall logically isolate from production networks any system with Critical severity vulnerabilities that remain unremediated past the timeline defined in this section,
 where no Risk Acceptance Memo has been approved under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The Network Administrator shall maintain logical isolation until remediation is complete or a Risk Acceptance Memo is in place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Unsupported Software (End-of-Life)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibition
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall not deploy or maintain software,
 firmware,
 or operating systems that have reached End-of-Life or End-of-Support status as declared by the vendor on County networks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Migration Plan
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall present a migration plan to the IT Director for any asset approaching End-of-Life,
 not later than ninety (90) calendar days prior to the vendor's declared End-of-Life date.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall approve the migration plan.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Continued-Use Compensating Controls
\series default
:
 Where End-of-Life software remains in use to support a critical business function,
 the IT Director shall require all of the following before authorizing continued use:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall obtain a Risk Acceptance Memo approved under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall enforce network isolation by air-gap or strict firewall segregation from the general County network and from external networks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall not permit CJI processing,
 storage,
 or transmission on the affected asset.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Verification and Rescanning
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Validation
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall verify remediation actions through a follow-up vulnerability scan or by manual verification within seven (7) calendar days of patch deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
False-Positive Disposition
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator or the Network Administrator who marks a vulnerability as a false positive shall validate the determination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator or the Network Administrator shall document supporting evidence for the false-positive determination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Systems Administrator or the Network Administrator shall record the false-positive disposition in the scanning tool.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall review false-positive designations no less frequently than annually for continued accuracy.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Reporting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Domain-Specific Inputs
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator and the Network Administrator shall each prepare monthly inputs covering open vulnerabilities by severity,
 Mean Time to Remediate (MTTR),
 patch compliance percentage,
 and the list of overdue assets within their respective domains.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compilation
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall compile the domain-specific inputs into a Monthly Vulnerability Compliance Report.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall perform cross-domain analysis prior to submission.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Submission
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall submit the Monthly Vulnerability Compliance Report to the IT Director not later than the tenth (10th) calendar day of the following month.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.9 Cloud and Third-Party Systems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Shared Responsibility
\series default
:
 For cloud-based systems,
 including Software-as-a-Service (SaaS),
 Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS),
 and Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS) deployments,
 the Assistant IT Director shall ensure that the contract or Service Level Agreement specifies the vendor's responsibility for vulnerability scanning and patch deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Vendor Vulnerability Assurance
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall evaluate vendor vulnerability management practices,
 including scan cadence,
 remediation timelines,
 and incident notification commitments,
 in coordination with the supply chain governance program defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall evaluate vendor security attestations,
 including Service Organization Control (SOC) 2 Type II reports and ISO/IEC 27001 certifications,
 specifically for vulnerability management adequacy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall evaluate FedRAMP authorization status for federal-tier cloud services in the asset inventory.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
